The paper deals with the problem of event retrieval using visual concepts, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of natural language processing techniques to extract relevant concepts from text descriptions also suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of weakly annotated web data for concept discovery and training is a common approach in multimedia analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed algorithm for pruning irrelevant concepts involves machine learning techniques, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
